=Description=

"In the coming age of extreme connectivity what will be important is not who you are, but what you are connected to. For the devices we use and the buildings we occupy in a wireless and ubiquitously networked world this will be even more vital: they will all need to communicate with each other and share information. Realtime interoperability between various types of entity will be essential. The world will become a vast 'eco-system' of conversant devices, buildings and virtual environments. Connected Environments Ltd. (CEL), headquartered in the heart of Silicon Roundabout, London, UK, is a company which focuses on exploiting these emerging trends and on delivering products and services that are intended to serve as the industry standard in this new and exciting area where technology, telecommunications and architecture are beginning to collide."



